                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.922/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Siam</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Baker</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-20T23:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 20, 1934—11 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.?</hi>]</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 20—3:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Referring to my telegram No. 11, August 18, noon.<note n="8" xml:id="d748fn8"
                        >Not printed.</note> Conditions here are such that I suggest the Department
                    suspend treaty negotiations pending developments. Air letter follows.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Baker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
